  "ciliary_role": "Orthologue of Chlamydomo s reinhardtii PF20, known to be essential to the structure and function of the motile axoneme. Encodes two proteins, SPAG16L and SPAG16S. SPAG16L is essential for sperm flagellar motility. Interacts with SPAG6, which in turn interacts with SPAG17. Mutation results in instability of interacting proteins in the central pair of the sperm axoneme. (16382026, 17699735). SPAG16S, identified only in male germ cells, plays a role in the gene expression machinery of male germ cells required for spermatogenesis, and it also modulates Spag16L mR  expression (21655194). Transcription of SPAG16 is regulated through S-SOX5 binding to the promoter (28137312).",
